Main 
- every Java program should have at least one class that contains a main method (class called main)
- whenever you run a Java program, the main method/function gets called
- main methods exist in a class

Class 
- a container for related functions, a blueprint for creating objects
- use PascalNamingConvenction = every word is uppercase

Methods
- use camelNamingConvention

Access Modifier
- classees and methods should have an access modifier
- a keyword that determines if other methods and classes in the program can access them (ex: public)


BASIC FORMAT OF A JAVA CLASS:

// create a class by giving it an access modifier, then use the "class" keyword, followed by a descriptive name 
public class Main {
  // main method
  public void main() {

  }
}




